correctness.rationale: Largely non-compliant and partially incorrect. Major issues: (1) Schema violations: many numeric fields are null, which is invalid (pressure.quantityValue.numericValue, growthPerCycle.values[*].value.quantityValue.numericValue, numberofCycles, dosingTime/purgeTime/flowRates numeric values, nucleationPeriod, uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, roughness.value, filmDensity.value, electricalProperties.*). (2) Placeholders not traceable to the article are used (carrierGas, purgingGas, reactor fields as 'Not Found'; saturation=True without evidence). (3) Mislabeling: deviceProperties.fieldEffectMobility set to 9.9 cm2/V·s, but 9.9 in the article is μ_sat (Fig. 2a), not μ_FE (SI shows μ_FE only for optimized devices), so this mapping is incorrect. (4) Supercycle design is inaccurately represented: article defines TEIn/In–Ga precursor/DEZn ratios of 0:2:2, 2:2:2, 4:2:2, but the JSON uses compounds InOx/GaOx/ZnO with counts 0/2/2 and labels the Ga step with an 'In-Ga precursor'—this does not faithfully reflect the In–Ga single-precursor subcycle described. (5) Multiple processes are not extracted: the paper reports distinct IGZO ALD processes/compositions (A, B, C at 150 °C with varying PL oxidants and D at 200 °C with O3 PL/GI), yet only one process is provided. (6) Including plasmaPower=None despite IGZO deposition being thermal ALD; if unused, this field should be omitted. Some correct elements are present (substrate SiO2/Si, film thickness 20 nm, O3 co-reactant for IGZO, TEIn/DEZn/In–Ga precursor, BGBC device structure, and composition A ratio 0.3:1:1.4 from Table 1), but the pervasive schema non-compliance, missing/placeholder values, incomplete multi-process coverage, and mis-mapped mobility warrant a rating of 1. Corrections needed: remove/replace all null and placeholder entries with article-grounded values; omit optional fields when unknown; accurately encode the supercycle as TEIn/In–Ga precursor/DEZn with counts per composition; separate processes for A, B (with H2O, O3, O2-plasma PL), C (O2-plasma PL), and D (200 °C, O3 PL/GI); use μ_FE only if reported (or omit fieldEffectMobility), and ensure all numerical values include valid QUDT units.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and schema‑noncompliant. Major issues: (1) Multiple processes not captured: the article reports distinct IGZO ALD supercycles and conditions—A (0:2:2, 150 °C), B (2:2:2, 150 °C), C (4:2:2, 150 °C), and D (2:2:2 at 200 °C)—and varied PL/GI oxidants (H2O, O3, O2-plasma), yet only a single process (composition A at 150 °C) is provided. Device metrics for other processes (e.g., μ_sat = 13.2, 17.1, 23.5, 27.6 cm2/V·s; SS values) are not represented as separate processes. (2) Many required properties are null or placeholders, violating the schema and the no-null requirement: pressure.numericValue=None; growthPerCycle values=None; numberofCycles=None; dosingTime, purgeTime, and all flowRates numericValue=None; nucleationPeriod=None; multiple materialProperties fields (uniformity, conformality, roughness, density) contain None; reactor, deliveryMethod, carrierGas, purgingGas are "Not Found". (3) Incoherences/mislabeling: deviceProperties.fieldEffectMobility is filled with μ_sat=9.9 cm2/V·s (the article distinguishes μ_sat vs μ_FE); threshold voltage and on/off ratio are omitted; supercycleDesign lists InOx with count 0 but still in subcycleSequence; missing supercycle counts for B and C (2:2:2 and 4:2:2) and D at 200 °C. (4) Available composition data from Table 1 (atomic % for A/B/C) is not populated in elementalConcentration; only composition A’s In:Ga:Zn ratio is given. (5) plasmaPower is present as null although PEALD was not used for IGZO; materialProperties.crystallinity lacks method; many fields use placeholders without traceable values. To be complete, add separate processes for A, B, C, and D with their specific supercycle ratios, temperatures, and gate‑stack oxidants; populate all required numerical fields with valid values/units or omit optional fields rather than using null; correct mobility type; include atomic % compositions from Table 1; and supply or clearly omit unavailable parameters (e.g., pressure, flow, dosing/purge times) per schema.
